==Esperanto==
===Etymology===
Esperanto ''[[ti-]]'' (demonstrative [[:Category:Esperanto correlatives|correlative]] prefix) + ''[[-a]]'' (correlative suffix of "kind")

===Correlative===
'''tia''' (''plural'' '''[[tiaj]]''', ''accusative singular'' '''[[tian]]''', ''accusative plural'' '''[[tiajn]]''')

# [[that]] kind of, such a (demonstrative correlative of kind)
#: As with other demonstrative correlatives in Esperanto, ''[[tia]]'' can be combined with ''[[ĉi]]'', the adverbial particle of proximity, or with ''[[for]]'', the adverbial particle of distance. ''Tia ĉi'' thus means ''this [as I am indicating] kind of'' and ''tia for'' means ''that [as someone else has indicated] kind of''.

